She flipped to an empty page and wrote down the date. Below that, she wrote "11.5.648–13.12.648".
"Freshing up old memories?" Ivory asked, looking at the old notebook. Kari nodded. "Do you think they'll let you out for Christmas? There are only a few days left."
Kari tapped twice on the lantern. "No," as Ivory had suspected. The Ice King never let Kari out, for he considered her a "flaw." She was born deaf and was the only daughter in the family, her siblings were all boys.
Something similar applied to Ivory as well. When Ivory came out as non-binary, it seemed as if the world itself was changing. As punishment for this difference, Ivory was given tasks where one spent most of the time alone.
Moreover, Ivory was also forced to serve the princess. It didn't bother Ivory much, since Ivory had also gained a friend.
"Are you having a birthday soon, right?" Ivory asked, thinking about the fact that the princess was having a birthday in a few days. Kari nodded with a sad flicker in her bright blue eyes.
"Would you like to celebrate your birthday?" Ivory asked, thinking about the last time the princess answered this question.
"No," Kari tapped. Ivory knew this was a difficult topic for her. Her birthday was the day she was locked in this room and her mother was banished. Ivory had been a baby at the time, but she remembered how upset the servants and the citizens of the city had been. Ivory had heard that Eirwen was a popular queen. And that she strangely could predict things that actually came true.
"Now, what do you want to do?" Ivory asked. Kari looked at Ivory excitedly. She was holding a piece of paper in her hand. On it was written:
15 x 15 cm canvas
Blue, various shades of blue
Brushes in six different sizes
Easel
"Are these things I should get for you?" Ivory turned to the silent princess, whose braids swayed back and forth from her vigorous knocking. "Yes?" Ivory giggled softly. The usually reserved princess showed so much excitement. It was the first time she had asked about something that had nothing to do with books and came from outside her room.
"Okay! Let's see each other later?" Ivory asked, stood up, and wove through the chaos of paper and notebooks.
Kari nodded, turned back to her notes, and wrapped herself in her blanket.
Ivory left the room, relieved that the princess had finally stepped out of her comfort zone and asked for things beyond her reach, like Malfarben.
Ivory ran through the corridors again and tried to ignore the gossip of the maids.
"I've heard that she is supposed to be possessed by Queen Eirwen and therefore goes into this room again and again."
"I've heard that she eats children in this room."
"Does she look like a man? That's not normal?"
Ivory covered her ears because she couldn't ignore the gossip any longer, and continued on. The room of the royal painter was located in the east wing behind the second door on the left side.
Ivory approached the door, which was just as intricately decorated as Kari's door. On it was the White Dragon, one of the six Primordial Dragons said to have supposedly created Frostfell. For a history-loving painter, the White Dragon on the door made perfect sense.
Ivory opened the door and expected the usual mess. Paint splatters everywhere, brushes and paper scattered around the room, easels covering every inch of the wall. Unexpectedly, a different scene presented itself. The entire room was clean, and against a background of red velvet stood a chair. On the chair sat Crown Prince Aquilo, who was just being painted.
"Good morning, Ivory! Would you like to watch as your future king is being painted?" asked Aquilo and winked at Ivory.
"Excuse me, little prince," said Ivory, mostly ignoring him and gathering the things the quiet princess wished for. "I'm only here to get art supplies."
"Would my little girl want to go already?" asked Aquilo. "But I want you to stay!"
"I don't either." Ivory found the art supplies on the list and placed them in a box. "Besides, I'm not a girl."
The prince was however of a different opinion. "Oh sweetie, that's just a phase! As you grow older, you'll grow out of it!" he said indistinctly.
"I have to go," said Ivory, feeling uneasy from the prince's answer. At that moment, Ivory recalled all the unpleasant remarks he and others had made about her gender identity in the past. I just want to be away from here.
"Are you leaving already?" Suddenly, the prince appeared at the door and ignored the loud objections of the royal painter.
"That is not behavior for a future king!" said Ivory.
"Nobody will find out. People won't believe you, and the painter will stay silent if his life is worth anything." He briefly looked at the painter and then leaned closer to Ivory. "What do you think about a date?" Ivory had been harassed multiple times in the past, but never by a prince, let alone the Crown Prince.
"Do you even know what the word 'No' means?" spat Ivory and pushed the Crown Prince away.
"No," replied Aquilo with a smile. Of course, the Crown Prince, who can have anything he wants, doesn't know what the word "No" means.
Ivory rolled her eyes. "Why would you want to go out with someone like me? You must have at least 100 admirers?"
"Actually, it's 50," he interrupted Ivory, still smiling. He甩ed his hair back, which whirled around in the cold air.
"Now get it! Why me? I'm a danger to the palace." Ivory crossed her arms.
"You are the most beautiful girl I have ever seen." Aquilo lifted Ivory's chin with his finger and forced her to look at him.
